。销售于 8 月 7 日结束。换句话说，如果您打算在空调门后摆弄乐器来消暑，请抓紧时间。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/reverbs-summer-sale-brings-deals-from-korg-uad-and-more-180322955.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/reverbs-summer-sale-brings-deals-from-korg-uad-and-more-180322955.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 16b2b102-5950-4dc2-9110-6498faf58ce8</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jul 2023 18:03:22 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690567403</ingested><modified> 2023-07-28T18:03:45+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Shopping]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hobbies & Personal Activities]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><media:content height="1060" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/19593a60-2d6c-11ee-b7f9-188811b9863a" width="1600"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1060" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/19593a60-2d6c-11ee-b7f9-188811b9863a" width="1600"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Universal Audio]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A Volt 276 along with a keyboard, microphone, speakers and headphones.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[UAD Volt 276]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indie games have entered the era of bespoke publishing]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>对于任何关注视频游戏新闻的人来说，很难忽视最近与独立项目相关的品牌的崛起，例如 Annapurna Interactive、Devolver Digital、Private Division、Humble、Epic Games 和 Netflix。在过去的几年里，独立开发商的发行流程已经从自我出版优先的模式转变为优先考虑交易和收购的模式。目前，这种转变正在推动独立游戏世界的小规模但引人注目的繁荣。</p><p> “我想我再也不想自行出版了。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Ben Ruiz 自 2005 年以来一直是一名游戏开发者，在那段时间里，他几乎完成了这一切。他创立了两个工作室，承包了<em>《Super Meat Boy》</em>和<em>《Overland》</em>等游戏，并独立出版了一个主打原创项目——单色格斗游戏<em>《Aztez》</em> 。如今，鲁伊斯经营着一家名为 Dinogod 的五人工作室，他正在开发<em>《Bounty Star》</em> ，这是一款将机甲战斗与生活模拟机制融为一体的游戏。 <em>《Bounty Star》</em>由 Annapurna Interactive 出版，预计于 2024 年初发行。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/345dee00-2d62-11ee-af79-59f02475f0a7" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="赏金之星" data-uuid="25f19b28-7859-35d5-b944-65032461b1a4"><figcaption>赏金之星</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">安纳普尔纳互动</div></figure><p>“似乎一切都对出版商关系有利，因为自我出版已经变得异常困难，”鲁伊斯说。 “这是可能的，但如果没有帮助，我就是不知道别人是怎么做到的……我有很多朋友也有同样的情况。”</p><p> Ruiz 的职业生涯是过去 10 年独立开发者格局变化的缩影。他于 2010 年开始开发<em>《Aztez》</em> ，当时 Steam 是一个精心策划的市场，Valve 员工为该平台手工挑选个别游戏。到 2012 年，这个系统已经完全崩溃：继<em>《时空幻境》</em> 、 <em>《超级食肉男孩</em>》和<em>《菲斯》</em>等热门游戏之后， <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2014-02-14-the-floating-fragile-indie-bubble.html">独立市场被新游戏和开发商占领</a>，Steam 放弃了其管理工作。它转向了一种名为<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2012-10-09-not-getting-noticed-on-steam-greenlight-incredipedes-story.html">Greenlight</a>的社区投票方法，然后最终采用了我们今天所知的一切皆可的抢先体验模式。</p><p> Ruiz 和他的商业伙伴在合同项目之间创建了<em>Aztez</em> ，当它准备于 2017 年在 Steam 上首次亮相时，独立市场已经饱和。 2010 年<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/552623/number-games-released-steam/">Steam 上新增了</a>309 款游戏； 2017年，这一数字为6,306。即使背后有大量的炒作，<em>阿兹特兹</em>也很难脱颖而出，那是鲁伊斯最后一次尝试自助出版。</p><p>在<em>阿兹特兹</em>之后，鲁伊斯做了一段时间的合同工作，并于 2018 年向他在安纳布尔纳峰认识的人推销了<em>赏金之星</em>。这款游戏有一个复杂的前提——主角克莱姆是一位背负着大量包袱的沙漠赏金猎人，涉及机甲战斗、情感叙事场景和家庭管理机制，包括一些轻型园艺。安纳布尔纳峰位，鲁伊斯达成了出版协议。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/641dcca0-2d67-11ee-9efe-9d606773e731" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="流浪" data-uuid="5e3747a9-2788-316f-b091-fd97f9ed08dd"><figcaption>流浪</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">安纳普尔纳互动</div></figure><p>Annapurna Interactive 是当今最著名的独立游戏发行商之一，其书籍包括<em>《Stray》</em> 、《 <em>Outer Wilds》</em> 、 <em>《Neon White</em> 》、 <em>《Donut County</em> 》和<em>《What Remains of Edith Finch</em> 》。它成立于 2016 年，是 Annapurna Pictures 的分支机构，并迅速建立了自己的艺术出版商品牌，专注于视觉创新和情感驱动的体验。 <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/watch-annapurna-interactives-showcase-here-at-3pm-et-180020145.html">它的展示</a>现在已成为游戏日历上的主要内容。</p><p> Annapurna 负责<em>Bounty Star</em>的营销工作，并且还为 Ruiz 的工作室 Dinogod 提供经济支持。当鲁伊斯推销这款游戏时，他很清楚他需要一支五到六人的团队来实现他的愿景，安纳普尔纳为他提供了招聘资金。</p><p> “事实上，Dinogod 有五名全职员工，这是合作关系的一部分，”鲁伊斯说。 “当一切都获得批准时，这是第一步，引进这五六个人……。如果[安纳普尔纳]正在做一件他们认为是好的事情，并且需要更多的人，那似乎完全没问题。就像，他们并不反对规模化。”</p><p>如今，不仅仅是安纳普尔纳与独立开发商达成此类交易。 Devolver Digital 是独立发行商的鼻祖，自 2009 年以来，它与小型开发团队合作发行了包括<em>《迈阿密热线》</em> 、《 <em>Hatoful Boyfriend</em> 》、 <em>《塔罗斯法则》</em> 、 <em>《Gris</em> 》、 <em>《Fall Guys</em> 》、 <em>《Inscryption</em> 》、 <em>《Weird West</em> 》和<em>《Cult of the Lamb</em> 》在内的热门游戏。还有 Humble、Private Division、Raw Fury、Epic Games、Finji、Gearbox、EA 和 Netflix，这些公司近年来都加大了独立发行力度。与此同时，微软的策略是简单地收购它喜欢的工作室，如今 Xbox 游戏工作室旗下拥有 23 名开发商。索尼也在采取类似的做法，尽管它拥有的工作室比微软少。微软和索尼还与独立游戏公司签署了数百项一次性协议，试图用源源不断的新体验来充实他们的流媒体库（Xbox Game Pass 和 PlayStation Plus Premium）。</p><p>这是独立开发者的新标准：确定最适合您游戏基调的发行商，进行推介，然后祈祷。即使是老牌工作室，例如<em>Device 6 的</em>创造者 Simogo，也已转向发行商优先的模式。 Simogo 的最新项目<em>《Sayonara Wild Hearts》</em>和<em>《Lorelei and the Laser Eyes》</em>是其与 Annapurna 合作的成果。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/92d48430-2d62-11ee-ba53-bedd364b129f" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="再见狂野之心" data-uuid="649a6423-601b-3382-a967-337624e498a8"><figcaption>再见狂野之心</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">安纳普尔纳互动</div></figure><p>Simogo 联合创始人 Simor Flesser 本月早些时候<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/simogo-tries-to-explain-the-mysteries-of-lorelei-and-the-laser-eyes-161941692.html">告诉 Engadget</a> ：“我认为，对于我们作为一个工作室来说，最大的变化是与出版商合作，这在十年前我们会认为完全无趣且不切实际。”</p><p>然后是 Netflix。这家流媒体公司于 2021 年正式进入游戏发行业务，预计到 2023 年底，其库中将拥有 100 款游戏，所有订阅 Netflix 的人都可以免费使用。它已经为移动设备带来了许多备受瞩目的游戏，包括<em>《Kentucky Route Zero</em> 》、 <em>《Poinpy</em> 》、《 <em>Into the Breach》</em> 、 <em>《Spiritfarer》</em> 、 <em>《Lucky Luna》</em>和<em>《Oxenfree II》</em> ，并且它还直接收购了一些工作室，尤其是<em>Alphabear</em>开发商 Spry Fox 和 Oxenfree house夜校工作室。第一个收购是 Netflix 于 2021 年收购的 Night School。</p><p> “整合——我并没有真正掌握这方面的脉搏，因为当我们加入 Netflix 时，感觉并没有发生得那么快，”Night School 联合创始人 Sean Krankel <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/why-the-oxenfree-ii-team-became-netflixs-first-game-studio-130035607.html">告诉 Engadget</a> 。 “而在过去的几年里，从字面上看，它是不间断的。”</p><p>克兰克尔表示，此次收购使 Night School 得以搬入 Netflix 办公室，并为整个工作室提供了稳定性。借助 Netflix 的资源，Night School 团队能够在<em>Oxenfree II</em>中添加对 32 种语言的第一天支持，并且他们能够根据需要与远程协作者一起飞行。</p><p> “这一切真的令人兴奋，” <em>Oxenfree II</em>首席开发人员 Bryant Cannon 在游戏 7 月 12 日发布之前说道。 “我认为游戏会变得更好，因为我们背后有这块电池。” </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/3c5d6860-2d67-11ee-8def-11e4af4dcd52" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="奥森弗里二世" data-uuid="025a3633-e0cd-32ec-ae99-803012746536"><figcaption>奥森弗里二世</figcaption><div class="photo-credit">Netflix</div></figure><p>除了收购之外，Netflix 还与开发商签署了单独的协议。 Snowman 因<em>《阿尔托的冒险》</em>和<em>《阿尔托的奥德赛》</em>而闻名，其最新项目是<em>《莱雅的地平线》</em> ，这是 Netflix 独家提供的宁静翼装体验。 There are two big benefits of working with Netflix, according to Snowman creative director Jason Medeiros: The instant access to an audience of more than 230 million people, and the freedom to build a game without worrying about monetization.</p><p> “You&#39;ll notice real quick that the game that you&#39;ve been playing can&#39;t be free-to-play,” Medeiros <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/layas-horizon-a-sandbox-wingsuit-game-from-the-studio-behind-altos-odyssey-arrives-may-2nd-150033749.html">told Engadget</a> in April. “Like, where would the ads go? It&#39;s this fantasy world with no currency, even, and all that&#39;s intentional. As the creative director, I didn&#39;t want any of that stuff. Because I mean, I liked games before all that stuff happened. So having a platform like Netflix, it&#39;s just like, none of that matters. You don&#39;t have to do that stuff. It&#39;s a breath of fresh air; we jump on opportunities to make games that way.”</p><p> Of course, there are still developers self-publishing their projects — <em>Vampire Survivors</em> , <em>Phasmophobia</em> , <em>Celeste</em> and <em>Among Us</em> are all standout examples — but there&#39;s a murkier path to success with this model, one based on timing, trends and a hefty amount of luck. There are more than 90,000 games on Steam today; Xbox Game Pass and PS Plus Premium libraries each have more than 400 titles (and counting). In this marketplace, it&#39;s hard to stand out without a little help.</p><p> It&#39;s taken 10 years to get here, but it&#39;s now a solid, quantifiable fact: There&#39;s a lot of money in indie games. So much money that outside companies are popping up and trying to get a piece of the pie — and for now, it&#39;s created a shiny bubble of pretty PR packages and bespoke showcases dedicated to small teams and their games. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/0ca7f490-2d63-11ee-bfff-19fdacb4b4bc" style="height:1080px;width:1920px;" alt="格里斯" data-uuid="5c0610d7-668d-3f20-8eff-b1c46a43b1b8"><figcaption> Gris</figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Devolver Digital</div></figure><p> It&#39;s difficult to ignore the potential for exploitation down the line, especially with Netflix in the mix. Amid the ongoing writers&#39; and actors&#39; strike, the company is facing accusations that it instituted wildly unfair compensation deals for creatives, paying out one-time, minimal wages even as projects became massive hits on the streaming service. Annapurna, for its part, was accused of mishandling claims of abuse at three prominent studios on its publishing roster — Mountains, Funomena and Fullbright — in a March 2022 documentary by <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xDPzZkx0cPs">People Make Games</a> . Meanwhile, the current consolidation craze is <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/summer-game-fest-2023-and-the-stagnant-state-of-the-industry-163019962.html">shrinking the video game industry</a> overall, even as the market caps of the biggest companies continue to rise.</p><p> For now, bespoke publishing is the name of the indie game. This system has already distributed innovative and important games to huge audiences — <em>Tchia</em> , <em>Tunic</em> , <em>Sea of Solitude</em> , <em>Gris</em> — and it&#39;s offered stability to a lot of independent artists. Like, for instance, Ben Ruiz.</p><p> “I hope Annapurna&#39;s success means more Annapurnas in the future,” Ruiz said. “It doesn&#39;t feel like they&#39;re just trying to grab a thing that will make money or collaborate with people that are just going to make them money. They clearly have a brand and an aesthetic directive … if I can keep making games for them for a long time, I will.”</p><p> The new normal works for Ruiz — and Flesser, Krankel, Medeiros and plenty of others. For now, it&#39;s a functional system, even if it ultimately leaves publishers, rather than independent developers, with most of the power.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/indie-games-have-entered-the-era-of-bespoke-publishing-170639414.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/indie-games-have-entered-the-era-of-bespoke-publishing-170639414.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1af4942f-a233-4da4-acea-5099ee7ab092</guid><dc:creator> Jessica Conditt</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jul 2023 17:06:39 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690564650</ingested><modified> 2023-07-28T17:17:41+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jessica Conditt]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/73775dd0-2d6a-11ee-8eb6-7bf768efa7e8" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/73775dd0-2d6a-11ee-8eb6-7bf768efa7e8" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Netflix]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[In this still from the video game 'Oxenfree II' two characters face each other on a bridge with a waterfall in the background and a triangular void in the air above them that seems to look into another colorful world.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Oxenfree II]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Emmys are reportedly delayed due to ongoing strikes]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> The Primetime Emmys won&#39;t take place on September 18th, <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/emmys-airdate-actors-writers-strike-1235681067/">according to</a> <em>Variety</em> . The publication reported on Thursday that vendors scheduled to work the event have been told the ceremony is delayed because of the writers&#39; and actors&#39; strikes that have shut down all Hollywood productions and promotions. The TV Academy hasn&#39;t yet announced a replacement date, but <em>Variety</em> previously <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://variety.com/2023/tv/news/emmys-strike-delay-fox-tv-academy-january-november-1235667092/">reported</a> that broadcast partner Fox tentatively wants to shoot for January 2024. HBO&#39;s <em>Succession</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/hbos-the-last-of-us-adaptation-scoops-up-24-emmy-nominations-171117148.html">leads this year&#39;s field</a> with 27 nominations, while <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-last-of-us-season-one-hbo-review-080135969.html"><em>The Last of Us</em></a> made history with an impressive 24 nods for the video game adaptation.</p><p> Hollywood writers <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/hollywood-writers-are-officially-on-strike-084059607.html">began striking</a> in early May, while actors joined them earlier this month. Artificial intelligence figures prominently in both cases: Scribes and performers fear producers will increasingly use AI-generated content to diminish humans&#39; ability to make a living in the already-brutal show business industry. Perhaps the most startling revelation was the report that studios offered a “groundbreaking AI proposal” to pay performers for one day of work to <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/striking-actors-say-rejected-ai-proposal-would-let-studios-use-their-likeness-without-fair-pay-000025878.html">use their digital likeness for eternity</a> . As generative AI advances quicker than most people could have imagined, it now threatens to <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/chatgpt-is-suddenly-everywhere-are-we-ready-180031821.html">annihilate content creators&#39; careers</a> inside and outside of Hollywood. </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/04a12d90-2d66-11ee-8df7-8203a9ade4f3" style="height:914px;width:2000px;" alt="Maarva (Fiona Shaw) in &#x002018;Andor.&#x002019; She sits in a fairly dark room with crude lighting equipment and a bright window behind her." data-uuid="c4463578-3342-3234-84c6-004f4d289b63"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Disney / Lucasfilm</div></figure><p> Although <em>The Last of Us</em> marked a milestone for gaming adaptations (including acting nominations for Pedro Pascal and Bella Ramsey), season three of Disney&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/dont-make-me-watch-boba-fett-to-understand-the-mandalorian-season-three-203004802.html"><em>The Mandalorian</em></a> received an impressive nine nominations. At the same time, <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/disney-bringing-andor-to-tv-and-hulu-193448433.html"><em>Andor</em></a> picked up eight nods — including Outstanding Drama Series. It recounts the journey of spy Cassian Andor (Diego Luna), one of the fallen heroes of 2016&#39;s <em>Rogue One</em> , in the period building up to the Rebel Alliance&#39;s rise against the Galactic Empire. <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/disney-plus-obi-wan-kenobi-baymax-173811314.html"><em>Obi-Wan Kenobi</em></a> , also on Disney+, received five more nominations, including Best Limited or Anthology Series.</p><p> In addition to <em>The Last of Us</em> and <em>Andor</em> , Outstanding Drama Series nominees include <em>Better Call Saul</em> , <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/house-of-the-dragon-game-of-thrones-hbo-youtube-premiere-episode-free-174317975.html"><em>House of the Dragon</em></a> , <em>Succession</em> , <em>The White Lotus</em> and <em>Yellowjackets</em> . </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/34566c90-2d65-11ee-8fef-9a8745c050b7" style="height:1125px;width:2000px;" alt="Jason Sudeikis as &#x002018;Ted Lasso.&#x002019; He&#x002019;s on a soccer field, leaning down and talking to a young boy." data-uuid="6f6b6ac4-c210-3c44-81bc-ab8064555b6c"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">苹果</div></figure><p>Apple TV+ also fared well in nominations, with 52. <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ted-lasso-season-three-preview-080056592.html"><em>Ted Lasso</em></a> is up for Best Comedy Series among its 21 nominations, which also include Best Actor in a Comedy Series for lead Jason Sudeikis, Best Supporting Actress in a Comedy for Hannah Waddingham and Best Supporting Actor in a Comedy for Phil Dunster. Apple&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-silo-review-wool-tv-show-123024485.html">mesmerizing sci-fi adaptation</a> <em>Silo</em> debuted too late for consideration this year, but don&#39;t be shocked if it features prominently in the 2024 list.</p><p> Elsewhere, Amazon&#39;s colossally ambitious <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/lord-of-the-rings-the-rings-of-power-was-amazon-primes-most-watched-debut-ever-075410830.html"><em>The Lord of the Rings: The Rings of Power</em></a> received six nods (mostly in technical categories). Netflix&#39;s <em>Stranger Things</em> picked up six, Peacock&#39;s <a data-i13n="cpos:15;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/poker-face-season-one-preview-160035861.html"><em>Poker Face</em></a> nabbed four and <a data-i13n="cpos:16;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/star-trek-picard-3-10-the-last-generation-review-140006372.html"><em>Star Trek: Picard</em></a> got two makeup nominations. HBO led all platforms with 127 nods, while Netflix led streaming-only networks with 103, followed by Apple (52) and Amazon (46).</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/the-emmys-are-reportedly-delayed-due-to-ongoing-strikes-164958589.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-emmys-are-reportedly-delayed-due-to-ongoing-strikes-164958589.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 5613b92c-5369-43c0-873f-bee7acaf57bb</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 28 Jul 2023 16:49:58 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1690563000</ingested><modified> 2023-07-28T16:50:06+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[Television]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="1394" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/72e4e600-2d63-11ee-baef-105abc83a10b" width="2482"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1394" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/72e4e600-2d63-11ee-baef-105abc83a10b" width="2482"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Jordan Strauss/Invision/AP]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Bella Ramsey, left, and Pedro Pascal arrive at a For Your Consideration red carpet for "Th